  49. ‌let overlap i0 i1 =
  50.   let rec overlap_ranges rl0 rl1 =
  51.     match rl0, rl1 with
  52.       r0 :: rl0', r1 :: rl1' ->
  53.         if r0.rend >= r1.rbegin && r1.rend >= r0.rbegin then true
  54.         else if r0.rend < r1.rend then overlap_ranges rl0' rl1
  55.         else if r0.rend > r1.rend then overlap_ranges rl0 rl1'
  56.         else overlap_ranges rl0' rl1'
  57.     | _ -> false in
  58.   overlap_ranges i0.ranges i1.ranges

  60. ‌let is_live i pos =

  64.                else if pos <= r.rend then true

  75. ‌let update_interval_position intervals pos kind reg =
  76.   let i = intervals.(reg.stamp) in
  77.   let on = pos lsl 1 in
  78.   let off = on + 1 in

  120. ‌let build_intervals fd =
  121.   let intervals = Array.init
  122.                     (Reg.num_registers())
  123.                     (fun _ -> {
  124.                       reg = Reg.dummy;
  125.                       ibegin = 0;
  126.                       iend = 0;
  127.                       ranges = []; }) in
  128.   let pos = ref 0 in
  129.   let rec walk_instruction i =
  130.     incr pos;
  131.     update_interval_position_by_instr intervals i !pos;
  132.     begin match i.desc with
  133.       Iend -> ()
  134.     | Iop(Icall_ind | Icall_imm _ | Iextcall{alloc = true; _}
  135.           | Itailcall_ind | Itailcall_imm _) ->
  136.         walk_instruction i.next
  137.     | Iop _ ->
  138.         insert_destroyed_at_oper intervals i !pos;
  139.         walk_instruction i.next
  140.     | Ireturn ->
  141.         insert_destroyed_at_oper intervals i !pos;
  142.         walk_instruction i.next
  143.     | Iifthenelse(_, ifso, ifnot) ->
  144.         insert_destroyed_at_oper intervals i !pos;
  145.         walk_instruction ifso;
  146.         walk_instruction ifnot;
  147.         walk_instruction i.next
  148.     | Iswitch(_, cases) ->
  149.         insert_destroyed_at_oper intervals i !pos;
  150.         Array.iter walk_instruction cases;
  151.         walk_instruction i.next
  152.     | Icatch(_, handlers, body) ->
  153.         insert_destroyed_at_oper intervals i !pos;
  154.         List.iter (fun (_, i) -> walk_instruction i) handlers;
  155.         walk_instruction body;
  156.         walk_instruction i.next
  157.     | Iexit _ ->
  158.         insert_destroyed_at_oper intervals i !pos;
  159.         walk_instruction i.next
  160.     | Itrywith(body, handler) ->
  161.         insert_destroyed_at_oper intervals i !pos;
  162.         walk_instruction body;
  163.         insert_destroyed_at_raise intervals !pos;
  164.         walk_instruction handler;
  165.         walk_instruction i.next
  166.     | Iraise _ ->
  167.         walk_instruction i.next
  168.     end in
  169.   walk_instruction fd.fun_body;
